title: Ghosts I Have Met and Some Others
creator: John Kendrick Bangs
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of Ghosts I Have Met and Some Others, by John Kendrick Bangs. Read by Cathy Barratt. New York-born John Kendrick Bangs was associate editor and then editor of Life and Harper magazines, eventually finding his way into the Humour department. Here he began to write his own satire and humour. Ghosts I Have Met and Some Others is a delightfully humourous collection of short tales relating encounters with ghosts. (Summary by Cathy Barratt) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
